attribute: "Driver Setup"
	"Inherent IVI Settings:Advanced Session Information:Driver Setup"
	string readonly local 00100597
"     Some cases exist where you must specify instrument driver options at initialization time.  An example of this is specifying a particular instrument model from among a family of instruments that the driver supports.  This is useful when using simulation.  
     You can specify driver-specific options through the DriverSetup keyword in the optionsString parameter to the Init With Options VI.  If you open an instrument using a logical name, you can also specify the options through the IVI Configuration Utility.
     The default value is an empty string.
     "
attribute: "Logical Name"
	"Inherent IVI Settings:Advanced Session Information:Logical Name"
	string readonly local 001006C1
"A string containing the logical name you specified when opening the current IVI session.
     You may pass a logical name to the Initialize or Initialize With Options VIs.  The IVI Configuration utility must contain an entry for the logical name.  The logical name entry refers to a virtual instrument section in the IVI Configuration file.  The virtual instrument section specifies a physical device and initial user options.
    "
attribute: "IO Resource Descriptor"
	"Inherent IVI Settings:Advanced Session Information:IO Resource Descriptor"
	string readonly local 001006C0
"Indicates the resource descriptor the driver uses to identify the physical device.
    If you initialize the driver with a logical name, this property contains the resource descriptor that corresponds to the entry in the IVI Configuration utility.  
    If you initialize the instrument driver with the resource descriptor, this property contains that value.
    "
attribute: "Output Mode"
	"Basic Operation:Output Mode"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC=0, IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB=1, IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ=2} readwrite local 001312D1
"Determines the kind of waveform the function generator produces.  The value you specify determines which VIs and properties you use to configure the waveform the function generator produces.
    When you set this property to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC, you use the following properties and VIs to configure standard waveforms:

IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Waveform
IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Amplitude
IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>DC Offset
IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Frequency
IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Start Phase
IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Duty Cycle High

Configure Standard Waveform

    When you set this property to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB, you use the following properties and VIs to configure arbitrary waveforms:

IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Arbitrary Waveform Handle
IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Arbitrary Waveform Gain
IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Arbitrary Waveform Offset
IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Sample Rate

Create Arbitrary Waveform
Clear Arbitrary Waveform
Configure Arbitrary Waveform
Configure Sample Rate
    If your instrument allows you to specify the rate at which an entire arbitrary waveform is generated, you can also use the following properties and VIs to configure arbitrary waveforms:

IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Arb Frequency

Configure Arb Frequency

    When you set this property to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ, you use the following properties and VIs to configure sequences:

IviFgen>>Arbitrary Sequence Output>>Arbitrary Sequence Handle
IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Arbitrary Waveform Gain
IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Arbitrary Waveform Offset
IviFgen>>Arbitrary Waveform Output>>Sample Rate

Create Arbitrary Sequence
Clear Arbitrary Sequence
Clear Arbitrary Memory
Configure Arbitrary Sequence
      
IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC 0
Configures the function generator to produce standard waveforms.

IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB 1
Configures the function generator to produce arbitrary waveforms.

IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ 2
Configures the function generator to produce sequences of arbitrary waveforms."
attribute: "Operation Mode"
	"Basic Operation:Operation Mode"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_OPERATE_CONTINUOUS=0, IVIFGEN_VAL_OPERATE_BURST=1} readwrite local 001312D5
"This property specifies how the function generator produces waveforms. For example, you can configure the instrument to generate output continuously, or to generate a discrete number of waveform cycles based on a trigger event.
      
IVIFGEN_VAL_OPERATE_CONTINUOUS 0
Configures the function generator to generate output continuously.

IVIFGEN_VAL_OPERATE_BURST 1
Configures the function generator to generate a burst of waveform cycles."
attribute: "Reference Clock Source"
	"Basic Operation:Reference Clock Source"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_REF_CLOCK_INTERNAL=0, IVIFGEN_VAL_REF_CLOCK_EXTERNAL=1, IVIFGEN_VAL_REF_CLOCK_RTSI_CLOCK=2} readwrite local 001312D2
"Specifies the reference clock source.  The function generator derives frequencies and sample rates that it uses to generate waveforms from the source you specify.
      
IVIFGEN_VAL_REF_CLOCK_INTERNAL 0
The function generator produces the reference clock internally.

IVIFGEN_VAL_REF_CLOCK_EXTERNAL 1
The function generator receives the reference clock signal from an external source.

IVIFGEN_VAL_REF_CLOCK_RTSI_CLOCK 2
The function generator receives the reference clock signal from the RTSI clock source."
attribute: "Output Enabled"
	"Basic Operation:Output Enabled"
	bool readwrite local 001312D3
"This channel-based property specifies whether the signal the function generator produces appears at the output connector.
      
TRUE 1
True

FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Output Impedance"
	"Basic Operation:Output Impedance"
	fD readwrite local 001312D4
"This channel-based property specifies the function generator's output impedance at the output connector.
      "
attribute: "Waveform"
	"Standard Function Output:Waveform"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_SINE=1, IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_SQUARE=2, IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_TRIANGLE=3, IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_RAMP_UP=4, IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_RAMP_DOWN=5, IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_DC=6} readwrite local 00131335
"This channel-based property specifies which standard waveform the function generator produces.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenStdFunc extension group.
    
IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_SINE 1
Configures the function generator to produce a sinusoid waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_SQUARE 2
Configures the function generator to produce a square waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_TRIANGLE 3
Configures the function generator to produce a triangle waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_RAMP_UP 4
Configures the function generator to produce a positive ramp waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_RAMP_DOWN 5
Configures the function generator to produce a negative ramp waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_DC 6
Configures the function generator to produce a constant voltage."
attribute: "Amplitude [STD]"
	"Standard Function Output:Amplitude [STD]"
	fD readwrite local 00131336
"This channel-based property specifies the amplitude of the standard waveform the function generator produces.  This value is the amplitude at the output terminal.  The units are volts peak-to-peak (Vpp).  For example, to produce a waveform ranging from -5.0 to +5.0 volts, you set this value to 10.0 volts.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC.  This property does not affect function generator behavior when you set the IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Waveform [STD] property to IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_DC.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenStdFunc [STD] extension group.
    "
attribute: "DC Offset [STD]"
	"Standard Function Output:DC Offset [STD]"
	fD readwrite local 00131337
"This channel-based property specifies the DC offset of the standard waveform the function generator produces.  This value is the offset at the output terminal.  The units are volts (V).  The value is the offset from ground to the center of the waveform you specify with the IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Waveform [STD] property.  For example, a standard waveform ranging from +5.0 volts to 0.0 volts has a DC offset of 2.5 volts.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenStdFunc [STD] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Frequency [STD]"
	"Standard Function Output:Frequency [STD]"
	fD readwrite local 00131338
"This channel-based property specifies the frequency of the standard waveform the function generator produces.  The units are hertz (Hz).  You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC.
    This property does not affect function generator behavior when you set the IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Waveform [STD] property to IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_DC.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenStdFunc [STD] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Start Phase [STD]"
	"Standard Function Output:Start Phase [STD]"
	fD readwrite local 00131339
"This channel-based property specifies the horizontal offset of the standard waveform the function generator produces.  You specify this property in degrees of one waveform cycle.  For example, a 180 degree phase offset means output generation begins half way through the waveform.  A start phase of 360 degrees offsets the output by an entire waveform cycle.  It is therefore identical to a start phase of 0 degrees.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC.  This property does not affect function generator behavior when you set the IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Waveform [STD] property to IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_DC.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenStdFunc [STD] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Duty Cycle High [STD]"
	"Standard Function Output:Duty Cycle High [STD]"
	fD readwrite local 0013133A
"This channel-based property specifies the length of time the output voltage level remains high in a square waveform.  You specify this property as a percentage of one waveform cycle.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_FUNC and the IviFgen>>Standard Function Output>>Waveform [STD] property to IVIFGEN_VAL_WFM_SQUARE.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenStdFunc [STD] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Arbitrary Waveform Handle [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Arbitrary Waveform Handle [ARB]"
	iL readwrite local 00131399
"This channel-based property identifies which arbitrary waveform the function generator produces.  You can create multiple arbitrary waveforms using the Create Arbitrary Waveform [ARB] VI.  The Create Arbitrary Waveform [ARB] VI returns a handle that you use to identify the particular waveform.  To configure the function generator to produce a particular waveform, you set this property to the waveform's handle.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Arbitrary Waveform Gain [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Arbitrary Waveform Gain [ARB]"
	fD readwrite local 0013139A
"This channel-based property specifies the factor by which the function generator scales the arbitrary waveform data.  When you create arbitrary waveforms, you must first normalize the data points to the range -1.0 to +1.0.  You use this property to scale the arbitrary waveform to other ranges.  For example, when you set this property to 2.0, the output signal ranges from -2.0 to +2.0 volts.
    You use this property when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB or IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Arbitrary Waveform Offset [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Arbitrary Waveform Offset [ARB]"
	fD readwrite local 0013139B
"This channel-based property specifies the value the function generator adds to the arbitrary waveform data.  When you create arbitrary waveforms, you must first normalize the data points to the range -1.0 to +1.0.  You use this property to shift the arbitrary waveform's range.The units are volts (V).  For example, when you set this property to 1.0, the output signal ranges from 2.0 volts to 0.0 volts.
    You use this property when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB or IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Sample Rate [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Sample Rate [ARB]"
	fD readwrite local 0013139C
"Specifies the rate at which the function generator outputs the points in arbitrary waveforms.  The units are samples per second.
    You use this property when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB or IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Arb Frequency [AF]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Arb Frequency [AF]"
	fD readwrite local 001313A1
"Specifies the rate at which the function generator outputs an entire arbitrary waveform.  The units are arbitrary waveforms per second.
    You use this property when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_ARB.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbFrequency [AF] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Max Number of Waveforms [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Max Number of Waveforms [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 0013139D
"Returns the maximum number of arbitrary waveforms that the function generator allows.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Waveform Quantum [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Waveform Quantum [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 0013139E
"The size of each arbitrary waveform must be a multiple of a quantum value.  This property returns the quantum value the function generator allows.
For example, when this property returns a value of 8, all waveform sizes must be a multiple of 8.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Min Waveform Size [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Min Waveform Size [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 0013139F
"Returns the minimum number of points the function generator allows in an arbitrary waveform.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Max Waveform Size [ARB]"
	"Arbitrary Waveform Output:Max Waveform Size [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 001313A0
"Returns the maximum number of points the function generator allows in an arbitrary waveform.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbWfm [ARB] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Arbitrary Sequence Handle [SEQ]"
	"Arbitrary Sequence Output:Arbitrary Sequence Handle [SEQ]"
	iL readwrite local 001313A3
"This channel-based property identifies which sequence the function generator produces.  You can create multiple sequences using the Create Arbitrary Sequence [SEQ] VI.  The Create Arbitrary Sequence [SEQ] VI returns a handle that you use to identify the particular sequence.  To configure the function generator to produce a particular sequence, you set this property to the sequence's handle.
    You use this property only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Output Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OUTPUT_SEQ.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbSeq [SEQ] extension group.
    
  "
attribute: "Max Number of Sequences [SEQ]"
	"Arbitrary Sequence Output:Max Number of Sequences [SEQ]"
	iL readonly local 001313A4
"Returns the maximum number of arbitrary sequences the function generator allows.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbSeq [SEQ] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Min Sequence Length [SEQ]"
	"Arbitrary Sequence Output:Min Sequence Length [SEQ]"
	iL readonly local 001313A5
"Returns the minimum number of arbitrary waveforms the function generator allows in a sequence.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbSeq [SEQ] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Max Sequence Length [SEQ]"
	"Arbitrary Sequence Output:Max Sequence Length [SEQ]"
	iL readonly local 001313A6
"Returns the maximum number of arbitrary waveforms the function generator allows in a sequence.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbSeq [SEQ] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Max Loop Count [SEQ]"
	"Arbitrary Sequence Output:Max Loop Count [SEQ]"
	iL readonly local 001313A7
"Returns the maximum number of times the function generator can repeat a waveform in a sequence.  Typically, this value is constant for the function generator.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenArbSeq [SEQ] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Trigger Source [TRG]"
	"Triggering:Trigger Source [TRG]"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_EXTERNAL=1, IVIFGEN_VAL_SOFTWARE_TRIG=2, IVIFGEN_VAL_INTERNAL_TRIGGER=3, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL0=111, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL1=112, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL2=113, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL3=114, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL4=115, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL5=116, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL6=117, IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL7=118, IVIFGEN_VAL_ECL0=119, IVIFGEN_VAL_ECL1=120, IVIFGEN_VAL_PXI_STAR=131, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_0=141, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_1=142, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_2=143, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_3=144, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_4=145, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_5=146, IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_6=147} readwrite local 001313FE
"This channel-based property specifies the trigger source. After the function generator receives a trigger, it generates an output signal based on the operation mode.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenTrigger [TRG] extension group.
    
IVIFGEN_VAL_EXTERNAL 1
The function generator waits for a trigger on the external trigger input.

IVIFGEN_VAL_SOFTWARE_TRIG 2
The function generator waits until you call the Send Software Trigger [SWT] VI.

IVIFGEN_VAL_INTERNAL_TRIGGER 3
The function generator waits for an internal trigger.

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL0 4
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG0 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL0 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL1 5
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG1 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL1 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL2 6
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG2 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL2 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL3 7
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG3 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL3 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL4 8
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG4 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL4 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL5 9
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG5 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL5 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL6 10
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG6 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL6 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_TTL7 11
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI TRIG7 line (for PXI instruments) or the VXI TTL7 line (for VXI instruments).

IVIFGEN_VAL_ECL0 12
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the VXI ECL0 line.

IVIFGEN_VAL_ECL1 13
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the VXI ECL1 line.

IVIFGEN_VAL_PXI_STAR 14
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on the PXI STAR trigger bus.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_0 15
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 0.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_1 16
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 1.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_2 17
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 2.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_3 18
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 3.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_4 19
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 4.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_5 20
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 5.

IVIFGEN_VAL_RTSI_6 21
The function generator waits until it receives a trigger on RTSI line 6."
attribute: "Internal Trigger Rate [IT]"
	"Triggering:Internal Trigger Rate [IT]"
	fD readwrite local 00131406
"This property specifies the rate at which the function generator's internal trigger source produces a trigger, in triggers per second.
This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Triggering>>Trigger Source [TRG] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_INTERNAL_TRIGGER on a channel.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenInternalTrigger [IT] extension group.
    "
attribute: "Burst Count [BST]"
	"Burst:Burst Count [BST]"
	iL readwrite local 0013142E
"This channel-based property specifies the number of waveform cycles that the function generator produces after it receives a trigger.
This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Basic Operation>>Operation Mode property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_OPERATE_BURST.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenBurst [BST] extension group.
    "
attribute: "AM Enabled [AM]"
	"Amplitude Modulation:AM Enabled [AM]"
	bool readwrite local 00131461
"This channel-based property specifies whether the function generator applies amplitude modulation to the output signal.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateAM [AM] extension group.
    
TRUE 1
True

FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "AM Source [AM]"
	"Amplitude Modulation:AM Source [AM]"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL=0, IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_EXTERNAL=1} readwrite local 00131462
"This channel-based property specifies the signal that the function generator uses to modulate the output signal.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateAM [AM] extension group.
    
IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL 0
Internal AM Modulating Source.

IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_EXTERNAL 1
External AM Modulating Source."
attribute: "AM Internal Depth [AM]"
	"Amplitude Modulation:AM Internal Depth [AM]"
	fD readwrite local 00131463
"Specifies the extent of modulation the function generator applies to the carrier signal.  The units are a percentage of full modulation.  At 0% depth, the output amplitude equals the carrier signal's amplitude.  At 100% depth, the output amplitude equals twice the the carrier signal's amplitude.
    This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Amplitude Modulation>>AM Source [AM] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateAM [AM] extension group.
    "
attribute: "AM Internal Waveform [AM]"
	"Amplitude Modulation:AM Internal Waveform [AM]"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_SINE=1, IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_SQUARE=2, IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_TRIANGLE=3, IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_RAMP_UP=4, IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_RAMP_DOWN=5} readwrite local 00131464
"Specifies the standard waveform type that the function generator uses to modulate the output signal.
    This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Amplitude Modulation>>AM Source [AM] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateAM [AM] extension group.
    
IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_SINE 1
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a sinusoid waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_SQUARE 2
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a square waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_TRIANGLE 3
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a triangle waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_RAMP_UP 4
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a positive ramp waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL_RAMP_DOWN 5
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a negative ramp waveform.
"
attribute: "AM Internal Frequency [AM]"
	"Amplitude Modulation:AM Internal Frequency [AM]"
	fD readwrite local 00131465
"Specifies the frequency of the standard waveform that the function generator uses to modulate the output signal.  The units are Hertz (Hz).
    This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Amplitude Modulation>>AM Source [AM] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_AM_INTERNAL.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateAM [AM] extension group.
    "
attribute: "FM Enabled [FM]"
	"Frequency Modulation:FM Enabled [FM]"
	bool readwrite local 001314C5
"Specifies whether the function generator applies frequency modulation to the output signal.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateFM [FM] extension group.
    
TRUE 1
True

FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "FM Source [FM]"
	"Frequency Modulation:FM Source [FM]"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL=0, IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_EXTERNAL=1} readwrite local 001314C6
"Specifies the signal the function generator uses to modulate the output signal.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateFM [FM] extension group.
    
IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL 0
Internal FM Modulating Source.

IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_EXTERNAL 1
External FM Modulating Source."
attribute: "FM Internal Deviation [FM]"
	"Frequency Modulation:FM Internal Deviation [FM]"
	fD readwrite local 001314C7
"Specifies the maximum frequency deviation the modulating waveform applies to the carrier waveform.  This deviation corresponds to the maximum amplitude level of the modulating signal.  The units are Hertz (Hz).
    This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Frequency Modulation>>FM Source [FM] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateFM [FM] extension group.
    "
attribute: "FM Internal Waveform [FM]"
	"Frequency Modulation:FM Internal Waveform [FM]"
	iL enum { IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_SINE=1, IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_SQUARE=2, IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_TRIANGLE=3, IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_RAMP_UP=4, IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_RAMP_DOWN=5} readwrite local 001314C8
"Specifies the standard waveform type that the function generator uses to modulate the output signal.
    This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Frequency Modulation>>FM Source [FM] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL.

Note:
(1) This property is part of the IviFgenModulateFM [FM] extension group.
    
IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_SINE 1
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a sinusoid waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_SQUARE 2
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a square waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_TRIANGLE 3
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a triangle waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_RAMP_UP 4
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a positive ramp waveform.

IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL_RAMP_DOWN 5
Configures the function generator to modulate the carrier signal with a negative ramp waveform.
"
attribute: "FM Internal Frequency [FM]"
	"Frequency Modulation:FM Internal Frequency [FM]"
	fD readwrite local 001314C9
"Specifies the frequency of the standard waveform that the function generator uses to modulate the output signal.  The units are Hertz (Hz).
    This property affects function generator behavior only when the IviFgen>>Frequency Modulation>>FM Source [FM] property is set to IVIFGEN_VAL_FM_INTERNAL.

Note:
